  <sharedRules>
    <rule name="Ammo runt" id="b0d5-e5d7-5df5-0bee" hidden="false">
      <description>**^^[Once per game]^^** One model in the unit after it has made a shooting attack with an **^^Assault type weapon^^** , may immidiately shoot again with that weapon as part of the same action or reaction, against the same target. (Use gretchin models as tokens for this ability)</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Bosspole" id="6d67-ee70-e7cd-5ed5" hidden="false">
      <description>**^^[Aura]^^** Units within 6” of a unit with a bosspole that fail a morale test in the morale phase may take one lethal damage to add 1 to the die result to the morale test, this may be done multiple times.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Cybork body" id="6446-7ef8-4604-4b05" hidden="false">
      <description>A model with a Cybork body has the **^^Feel no Pain (8+)^^** special rule</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Eavy armour" id="69a3-7b9a-4fd3-dffc" hidden="false">
      <description>A model with ’Eavy armour has a 7+ Armour save.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Gitfinda" id="1084-a4b0-c949-c64a" hidden="false">
      <description>A model with a Gitfinda that stays ^^**stationary**^^, it gains a +2 to hit rolls with its ranged attacks in that activation or reaction.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Dakka dakka" id="5c38-9b26-d971-4c54" hidden="false">
      <description>For each unmodified ranged weapon hit roll result of 10, the attack scores one additional successful hit.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Ere we go" id="4c70-3312-02c8-4ccb" hidden="false">
      <description>A unit with this ability may re-roll the charge roll die results of 1</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Breaking’ heads" id="d8ea-4624-f501-ca14" hidden="false">
      <description>^^**[Aura]**^^ if a friendly unit within 6” fails a morale test, this unit may deal 1d3 lethal wounds to that unit but the Morale test is then considered to have been succesfull.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Mob rule" id="df1e-2046-29fd-4534" hidden="false">
      <description>If a ork unit consists of 11 or more total wounds, it has the fearless special rule.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Oddboy" id="a3bd-6faf-c58f-20fb" hidden="false">
      <description>All models in this unit must separately join a friendly non-character infantry unit before deployment. Combining the separate model and the unit together as one. When a unit with this ability does so it loses the character keyword as long it is not joined with a unit. Any infantry unit can only be joined with up to one Oddboy.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Mek&apos;s tools" id="175f-4950-9017-3f6d" hidden="false">
      <description>^^**[Command ability]**^^  Target one friendly vehicle model within 6” and roll 2d10. That vehicle regains 1 wound for every result of 6+ and loses one wound for every result of 1. A vehicle can only regain wounds this way once per round.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Big Mek&apos;s tools" id="6d77-90c7-eb7a-2a4b" hidden="false">
      <description>^^**[Command ability]**^^ Target one friendly vehicle model within 6” and roll 4d10. That vehicle regains 1 wound for every result of 6+ and loses one wound for every result of 1. A vehicle can only regain wounds this way once per round.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Ramshackle" id="6ca6-5d73-cc38-6c39" hidden="false">
      <description>If an armour save die roll result of 1 is rolled with this vehicle, halve the damage of that attack (minimum 1).</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Shokk attack" id="8d70-e56a-a242-77b8" hidden="false">
      <description>Before declaring targets with the weapon roll 2d6+2 to determine the weapons Strength for that attack sequence. If a double is rolled with the 2d6 then consult the chart below the weapon profile.


^^**2D6 Result:**^^

^^**1-1 Boom:**^^ The weapon does not fire, instead it explodes and the
wielder of the weapon is slain, remove it as a casualty. In addition this model also explodes as if its a vehicle with 10-15 wounds.


^^**2-2 Oops:**^^ The wielder has trouble operating the weapon, instead
the opponent may choose new targets for the weapon, friend or
foe.


^^**3-3 Gah:**^^ The weapon fires at the closest visible unit (not itself)
instead, friend or foe.


^^**4-4 Sploosh:**^^ The weapon Type becomes Heavy 20 and the dam-
age changes to 1 for this attack sequence.


^^**5-5 Zoink:**^^ The weapon gains the Twin-linked special rule for
this attack sequence. The wielder of this weapon after attacking is
placed within 2” of the original target (within ingagement range
is allowed), if the target is destroyed place this model as close as
where the target originally was.


^^**6-6 Raargh:**^^ The weapon gains the Instant death special rule and
its damage is changed to 6, for this attack sequence.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Kustom force field" id="eadb-320d-fbe3-62ea" hidden="false">
      <description>^^**[Aura]**^^ This model, and all infantry models within 6”, receive a 8+ invulnerable save against any ranged attacks. If the model is embarked in a vehicle or is a vehicle, then the vehicle receives a 8+ invulnerable save against any ranged attacks instead.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Da Warboss" id="bdd3-8a9d-f295-4c25" hidden="false">
      <description>^^**[Command ability]**^^ Target one friendly infantry or cavalry unit within 6”, that unit either gains the Furious charge special rule OR gains the Twin linked special rule on all its ranged weapons, until the end phase.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
